WEBVTT

00:01.750 --> 00:05.250
<i>Captain's Log,</i>

00:01.750 --> 00:05.250
<i>Stardate 43872.2.</i>

00:05.291 --> 00:09.000
<i>In order to neutralize</i>

00:05.291 --> 00:09.000
<i>a sudden contamination</i>

00:05.291 --> 00:09.000
<i>of the water supply</i>

00:09.041 --> 00:11.667
<i>at the Federation colony</i>

00:09.041 --> 00:11.667
<i>on Beta Agni Two,</i>

00:11.709 --> 00:14.875
<i>we are procuring 108 kilos</i>

00:11.709 --> 00:14.875
<i>of hytritium</i>

00:14.917 --> 00:17.875
<i>from the Zibalian trader,</i>

00:14.917 --> 00:17.875
<i>Kivas Fajo.</i>

00:17.917 --> 00:21.625
<i>Because pure hytritium</i>

00:17.917 --> 00:21.625
<i>is too unstable</i>

00:17.917 --> 00:21.625
<i>for our transporters,</i>

00:21.667 --> 00:23.250
<i>Lieutenant Commander Data</i>

00:23.291 --> 00:26.208
<i>has been shuttling the material</i>

00:23.291 --> 00:26.208
<i>to the</i> Enterprise.

00:28.041 --> 00:29.583
Data to<i> Enterprise.</i>

00:29.625 --> 00:31.250
PICARD:

00:29.625 --> 00:31.250
Go ahead, Mr. Data.

00:31.291 --> 00:32.917
This will be the last trip,

00:31.291 --> 00:32.917
sir.

00:32.959 --> 00:35.375
The remaining cases of hytritium

00:32.959 --> 00:35.375
are now being loaded.

00:35.417 --> 00:36.542
Acknowledged.

00:36.583 --> 00:39.375
Mr. Worf,

00:36.583 --> 00:39.375
advise Beta Agni Two

00:39.417 --> 00:40.333
that our departure is imminent.

00:40.375 --> 00:42.083
WORF:

00:40.375 --> 00:42.083
Aye, Captain.

00:42.125 --> 00:45.583
At warp six, we should be there

00:42.125 --> 00:45.583
at just over 16 hours.

00:49.458 --> 00:50.959
Loading is complete.

00:51.000 --> 00:53.542
I am now proceeding

00:51.000 --> 00:53.542
with departure.

00:53.583 --> 00:56.750
<i>Enterprise</i> shuttle bay two,

00:53.583 --> 00:56.750
prepare for docking.

00:56.792 --> 01:00.917
Level one precautions

00:56.792 --> 01:00.917
for incoming material

01:00.959 --> 01:02.417
remain in effect.

01:02.458 --> 01:05.667
If you'll just acknowledge

01:02.458 --> 01:05.667
this last load, Commander.

01:17.792 --> 01:21.500
26.8 kilos tripolymer

01:17.792 --> 01:21.500
composites.

01:21.542 --> 01:24.875
11.8 kilos

01:21.542 --> 01:24.875
molybdenum-cobalt alloy.

01:24.917 --> 01:27.667
1.3 kilos bioplast sheeting.

01:31.291 --> 01:35.041
LA FORGE:

01:31.291 --> 01:35.041
Shuttle 12 containment field

01:31.291 --> 01:35.041
reads nominal.

01:35.083 --> 01:37.166
Now leaving the<i> Jovis.</i>

01:37.208 --> 01:39.000
On viewer.

01:42.417 --> 01:44.166
Containment field stable.

01:44.208 --> 01:47.959
Gravitational fluctuations

01:44.208 --> 01:47.959
within acceptable parameters.

01:48.000 --> 01:49.417
Flight pattern...

02:02.500 --> 02:04.792
Data.

02:33.750 --> 02:37.834
PICARD:

02:33.750 --> 02:37.834
<i>Space, the final frontier.</i>

02:37.875 --> 02:42.625
<i>These are the voyages</i>

02:37.875 --> 02:42.625
<i>of the starship</i> Enterprise.

02:42.667 --> 02:44.875
<i>Its continuing mission--</i>

02:44.917 --> 02:47.917
<i>to explore</i>

02:44.917 --> 02:47.917
<i>strange new worlds,</i>

02:47.959 --> 02:52.917
<i>to seek out new life</i>

02:47.959 --> 02:52.917
<i>and new civilizations,</i>

02:52.959 --> 02:58.041
<i>to boldly go</i>

02:52.959 --> 02:58.041
<i>where no one has gone before.</i>

03:56.542 --> 03:58.208
<i>Captain's Log, supplemental.</i>

03:58.250 --> 04:01.041
<i>As the result of a yet</i>

03:58.250 --> 04:01.041
<i>unexplained shuttle explosion,</i>

04:01.083 --> 04:04.709
<i>Lieutenant Commander Data</i>

04:01.083 --> 04:04.709
<i>has been lost.</i>

04:04.750 --> 04:05.875
RIKER: Why didn't the

04:04.750 --> 04:05.875
containment field hold?

04:05.917 --> 04:07.709
LA FORGE:

04:05.917 --> 04:07.709
Unknown, Commander.

04:07.750 --> 04:09.375
Hail the<i> Jovis.</i> I want to speak

04:07.750 --> 04:09.375
with Kivas Fajo.

04:09.417 --> 04:12.083
Sir, Mr. Fajo

04:09.417 --> 04:12.083
is hailing<i> us.</i>

04:12.125 --> 04:13.250
On viewer.

04:13.291 --> 04:16.417
Captain Picard,

04:13.291 --> 04:16.417
what happened?

04:16.458 --> 04:17.750
It's unclear.

04:17.792 --> 04:19.375
We're running

04:17.792 --> 04:19.375
a full analysis.

04:19.417 --> 04:22.083
We detected no malfunctions

04:19.417 --> 04:22.083
before the explosion.

04:22.125 --> 04:23.375
Everything seemed to be running

04:23.417 --> 04:24.875
as smoothly

04:23.417 --> 04:24.875
as the other flights.

04:24.917 --> 04:27.667
Were you able to save the pilot?

04:27.709 --> 04:29.709
No.

04:29.750 --> 04:32.208
I'm sorry.

04:32.250 --> 04:35.917
Mr. Fajo,

04:32.250 --> 04:35.917
I would like to analyze

04:35.959 --> 04:38.583
your sensor readings

04:35.959 --> 04:38.583
of the explosion.

04:38.625 --> 04:41.125
Compared to the<i> Enterprise's,</i>

04:38.625 --> 04:41.125
our sensors are

04:41.166 --> 04:43.083
rather primitive.

04:43.125 --> 04:46.375
I doubt they contain any

04:43.125 --> 04:46.375
information that your sensors

04:43.125 --> 04:46.375
overlooked.

04:46.417 --> 04:49.458
Perhaps, but I don't want to

04:46.417 --> 04:49.458
leave any avenue unexplored.

04:49.500 --> 04:51.542
I understand.

04:51.583 --> 04:55.875
We'll transmit the information.

04:55.917 --> 04:57.667
Link established.

04:57.709 --> 04:58.959
Receiving.

04:59.000 --> 05:01.291
Can we be of any further

04:59.000 --> 05:01.291
assistance?

05:01.333 --> 05:03.750
How much hytritium

05:01.333 --> 05:03.750
did we manage

05:01.333 --> 05:03.750
to bring on board?

05:03.792 --> 05:05.500
81 kilos.

05:05.542 --> 05:07.375
That may barely allow us to

05:05.542 --> 05:07.375
complete our mission, Captain,

05:07.417 --> 05:08.959
but it leaves us no margin

05:07.417 --> 05:08.959
for error.

05:09.000 --> 05:11.500
Mr. Fajo, I realize we have

05:09.000 --> 05:11.500
acquired

05:11.542 --> 05:13.750
your entire supply

05:11.542 --> 05:13.750
of hytritium.

05:13.792 --> 05:15.834
Do you know where

05:13.792 --> 05:15.834
we could obtain some more?

05:15.875 --> 05:19.291
That may be difficult.

05:15.875 --> 05:19.291
The only source I know is in

05:15.875 --> 05:19.291
the Sigma Erani system?

05:19.333 --> 05:20.750
Three weeks away, sir.

05:20.792 --> 05:23.125
And I can't guarantee

05:20.792 --> 05:23.125
they'll have any.

05:23.166 --> 05:25.375
For obvious reasons, no one

05:23.166 --> 05:25.375
wants to keep it around.

05:25.417 --> 05:28.458
In fact, even I may stop

05:25.417 --> 05:28.458
selling it.

05:28.500 --> 05:30.542
It's just too dangerous.

05:30.583 --> 05:32.625
I guess we're fortunate

05:30.583 --> 05:32.625
you had any at all, sir.

05:32.667 --> 05:35.625
Captain, transfer of

05:32.667 --> 05:35.625
information complete.

05:35.667 --> 05:37.834
Mr. Fajo...

05:37.875 --> 05:40.041
thank you for your help.

05:43.458 --> 05:46.458
Mr. Crusher, set a course for

05:43.458 --> 05:46.458
the Beta Agni Two system.

05:43.458 --> 05:46.458
Warp six.

05:46.500 --> 05:47.834
Aye, sir.

05:47.875 --> 05:49.542
The<i> Grissom's</i> near the

05:47.875 --> 05:49.542
Sigma Erani system.

05:49.583 --> 05:51.959
I'll alert them to stand by in

05:49.583 --> 05:51.959
case we need more hytritium.

05:52.000 --> 05:53.125
Thank you, Number One.

05:53.166 --> 05:55.750
Course laid in, sir.

05:59.458 --> 06:01.625
Engage.

06:35.583 --> 06:37.583
What am I doing here?

06:37.625 --> 06:38.709
(<i> door opens</i> )

06:44.333 --> 06:47.875
Oh. Wondrous.

06:47.917 --> 06:51.583
The detail, the balance.

06:53.542 --> 06:56.500
Was I not right, Varria?

06:56.542 --> 07:01.333
Oh, what a remarkable

06:56.542 --> 07:01.333
piece of work, hmm?

07:01.375 --> 07:03.041
Why have I

07:01.375 --> 07:03.041
been brought here?

07:03.083 --> 07:04.709
Oh!

07:04.750 --> 07:07.083
The... the voice simulation.

07:07.125 --> 07:09.041
It's... it's perfection.

07:09.083 --> 07:11.458
The inflections,

07:09.083 --> 07:11.458
the timing.

07:11.500 --> 07:13.417
(<i> snapping fingers</i> )

07:13.458 --> 07:14.917
(<i> laughing</i> )

07:14.959 --> 07:16.291
(<i> clears throat</i> )

07:16.333 --> 07:20.959
Yes, uh, it took great

07:16.333 --> 07:20.959
effort, effort...

07:21.000 --> 07:23.125
to bring you here.

07:23.166 --> 07:24.542
I was sure

07:23.166 --> 07:24.542
it would be worth it.

07:24.583 --> 07:25.792
I was right.

07:25.834 --> 07:27.750
I've been delivered here

07:25.834 --> 07:27.750
against my wishes.

07:27.792 --> 07:29.375
I would like

07:27.792 --> 07:29.375
to know the reason.

07:29.417 --> 07:30.834
Certainly.

07:30.875 --> 07:35.125
You have been brought here

07:30.875 --> 07:35.125
for my... enjoyment

07:35.166 --> 07:38.291
and my appreciation.

07:38.333 --> 07:41.291
Am I to infer that you intend

07:38.333 --> 07:41.291
to keep me captive?

07:41.333 --> 07:42.667
Captive? Captive?

07:42.709 --> 07:45.166
Oh, it's such

07:42.709 --> 07:45.166
an inappropriate description.

07:45.208 --> 07:48.750
My dear android...

07:48.792 --> 07:50.208
may I call you Data?

07:50.250 --> 07:52.291
It is my name.

07:52.333 --> 07:58.208
Data, you will be catered to,

07:52.333 --> 07:58.208
fawned over,

07:58.250 --> 08:00.083
cared for as you never

07:58.250 --> 08:00.083
have been before.

08:00.125 --> 08:04.125
Your every wish

08:00.125 --> 08:04.125
will be fulfilled.

08:04.166 --> 08:06.667
I wish to leave.

08:06.709 --> 08:09.166
Almost every wish.

08:09.208 --> 08:10.583
This is unacceptable, sir.

08:10.625 --> 08:13.542
I have no desire to remain here,

08:10.625 --> 08:13.542
and even if I did,

08:13.583 --> 08:15.959
my Starfleet duties

08:13.583 --> 08:15.959
would not allow it.

08:16.000 --> 08:19.792
It's so...

08:16.000 --> 08:19.792
single-minded, isn't it?

08:19.834 --> 08:21.500
Very persistent.

08:21.542 --> 08:24.250
But it's polite,

08:21.542 --> 08:24.250
which is a very nice touch.

08:24.291 --> 08:26.792
I decline to allow you to go.

08:26.834 --> 08:30.625
Then I am forced

08:26.834 --> 08:30.625
to attempt escape.

08:35.959 --> 08:38.291
Uh, ten androids

08:38.333 --> 08:41.500
just like you<i> might</i> be able

08:38.333 --> 08:41.500
to force that thing open.

08:41.542 --> 08:44.709
But then again, there aren't any

08:41.542 --> 08:44.709
more just like you, are there?

08:44.750 --> 08:47.667
It's keyed to galvanic

08:44.750 --> 08:47.667
skin responses

08:47.709 --> 08:49.875
and DNA patterns.

08:49.917 --> 08:51.625
Sorry.

08:51.667 --> 08:53.583
Then you will have to open it

08:51.667 --> 08:53.583
for me.

09:07.500 --> 09:09.709
Oh.

09:09.750 --> 09:14.083
Really, I wouldn't do that

09:09.750 --> 09:14.083
again if I were you.

09:14.125 --> 09:16.792
This is a proximity-actuated

09:14.125 --> 09:16.792
field.

09:16.834 --> 09:18.375
It impedes positron flow.

09:18.417 --> 09:21.917
It's very bad for the brain

09:18.417 --> 09:21.917
paths in the long term.

09:21.959 --> 09:26.083
I fail to understand

09:21.959 --> 09:26.083
the value you place

09:21.959 --> 09:26.083
on my presence.

09:26.125 --> 09:27.917
Well, just look

09:26.125 --> 09:27.917
around the room.

09:27.959 --> 09:30.208
There are items here gathered

09:27.959 --> 09:30.208
from half the galaxy.

09:30.250 --> 09:32.000
Right here--

09:32.041 --> 09:37.667
this is the very first basotile

09:32.041 --> 09:37.667
ever created.

09:41.166 --> 09:44.583
Oh, sorry.

09:44.625 --> 09:46.792
It's very, very ancient.

09:46.834 --> 09:48.792
Hundreds of years old.

09:48.834 --> 09:51.083
Oh, it's priceless.

09:51.125 --> 09:53.333
Come. This vase?

09:53.375 --> 09:56.542
This vase is made

09:53.375 --> 09:56.542
by Mark Off...

09:56.583 --> 09:59.542
the late Mark Off-Zel

09:56.583 --> 09:59.542
from Sirrie-Four.

09:59.583 --> 10:01.792
A Dali.

10:01.834 --> 10:03.291
This...

10:03.333 --> 10:06.834
this is the only known

10:03.333 --> 10:06.834
Roger Maris trading card

10:06.875 --> 10:10.709
from Earth, circa 1962.

10:15.041 --> 10:17.333
The smell?

10:17.375 --> 10:20.875
Bubble gum--

10:17.375 --> 10:20.875
I've preserved the scent.

10:20.917 --> 10:23.166
Ah.

10:23.208 --> 10:24.792
Uh... what, what?

10:24.834 --> 10:26.875
Ah, a lapling.

10:26.917 --> 10:28.750
(<i> humming</i> )

10:31.500 --> 10:33.875
I thought they were extinct.

10:33.917 --> 10:35.709
Extinct? Oh, good.

10:35.750 --> 10:39.125
Yes, well, that is what

10:35.750 --> 10:39.125
is generally believed.

10:39.166 --> 10:42.750
She is the last surviving

10:39.166 --> 10:42.750
member of her species.

10:42.792 --> 10:44.208
(<i> humming</i> )

10:44.250 --> 10:45.583
(<i> chuckles</i> )

10:45.625 --> 10:48.208
(<i> humming</i> )

10:51.208 --> 10:54.500
They're very defenseless

10:51.208 --> 10:54.500
creatures, really.

10:54.542 --> 10:58.625
Everything that you see

10:54.542 --> 10:58.625
in the room here, everything,

10:58.667 --> 11:01.166
one of a kind, unique.

11:01.208 --> 11:03.166
All original.

11:03.208 --> 11:05.250
Just as you are.

11:05.291 --> 11:08.667
There, that is your

11:05.291 --> 11:08.667
place of honor.

11:08.709 --> 11:10.750
(<i> chuckles</i> )

11:10.792 --> 11:12.959
Sit, sit.

11:13.000 --> 11:14.625
Sit.

11:16.375 --> 11:19.500
You think perhaps it might

11:16.375 --> 11:19.500
be uncomfortable?

11:19.542 --> 11:21.792
But then again, you don't give a

11:19.542 --> 11:21.792
thought to comfort, do you?

11:21.834 --> 11:25.750
When Palor Toff learns of that,

11:25.792 --> 11:27.291
he'll swallow his tongue

11:25.792 --> 11:27.291
with envy.

11:27.333 --> 11:30.125
I can't wait to see his face.

11:30.166 --> 11:32.291
You... you are, um...

11:32.333 --> 11:36.041
the crown jewel

11:32.333 --> 11:36.041
of my collection.

11:36.083 --> 11:38.625
You're a treasure

11:36.083 --> 11:38.625
beyond comparison.

11:38.667 --> 11:41.041
(<i> beeping</i> )

11:41.083 --> 11:43.250
Yes, go ahead.

11:46.333 --> 11:49.208
I think you should be flattered.

11:49.250 --> 11:50.875
I am not, sir.

11:50.917 --> 11:54.667
Most intelligent life-forms

11:50.917 --> 11:54.667
find involuntary confinement

11:54.709 --> 11:56.417
offensive and inequitable.

11:56.458 --> 11:58.625
Moreover, you have violated

11:56.458 --> 11:58.625
Federation law--

11:58.667 --> 12:00.417
I know, I know.

12:00.458 --> 12:03.750
What I've done is evil, selfish,

12:00.458 --> 12:03.750
immoral, unprincipled, illegal.

12:03.792 --> 12:06.667
Well I've learned to

12:03.792 --> 12:06.667
live with it.

12:06.709 --> 12:08.417
The Andorians

12:06.709 --> 12:08.417
wish to make a bid

12:08.458 --> 12:10.875
on the shipment

12:08.458 --> 12:10.875
of Tellurian spices you offered.

12:10.917 --> 12:13.041
They've had four days to decide!

12:13.083 --> 12:15.542
Why do they decide right--

12:13.083 --> 12:15.542
All right.

12:18.083 --> 12:21.166
I must emphasize,

12:18.083 --> 12:21.166
Mr. Fajo,

12:21.208 --> 12:25.291
that I consider this captivity

12:21.208 --> 12:25.291
a hostile act on your part.

12:25.333 --> 12:28.750
Oh. Well, you'll

12:25.333 --> 12:28.750
get used to it.

12:33.333 --> 12:35.750
(<i> screeches</i> )

12:50.000 --> 12:52.625
I can't believe he's gone.

12:52.667 --> 12:56.834
Yeah, well I always thought

12:52.667 --> 12:56.834
he'd outlive us by centuries.

12:56.875 --> 13:01.250
He'd been working on this

12:56.875 --> 13:01.250
for months.

13:01.291 --> 13:04.583
Never felt it was

13:01.291 --> 13:04.583
quite finished.

13:04.625 --> 13:06.667
You know what a critic

13:04.625 --> 13:06.667
Data was,

13:06.709 --> 13:08.875
especially about

13:06.709 --> 13:08.875
his own work.

13:29.333 --> 13:31.291
That was a gift from the

13:29.333 --> 13:31.291
captain.

13:33.250 --> 13:35.792
And he should have it back.

13:43.375 --> 13:45.333
Those should go

13:43.375 --> 13:45.333
to Commander Riker.

13:45.375 --> 13:49.208
Data always fell

13:45.375 --> 13:49.208
for Riker's bluffs.

13:50.208 --> 13:51.959
(<i> whistles</i> )

14:00.166 --> 14:03.458
These are some of Starfleet's

14:00.166 --> 14:03.458
highest honors.

14:03.500 --> 14:04.834
Not bad for a walking

14:03.500 --> 14:04.834
pile of circuitry

14:04.875 --> 14:07.083
and memory cells.

14:25.458 --> 14:28.083
You know,

14:28.125 --> 14:31.291
I keep going over and over

14:28.125 --> 14:31.291
the accident in my mind

14:31.333 --> 14:33.291
trying to figure out

14:31.333 --> 14:33.291
what went wrong.

14:33.333 --> 14:36.375
I can see Data

14:33.333 --> 14:36.375
in the shuttle

14:36.417 --> 14:38.583
almost like

14:36.417 --> 14:38.583
I'm sitting there next to him

14:38.625 --> 14:42.959
going through

14:38.625 --> 14:42.959
the departure sequence.

14:43.000 --> 14:46.333
What the hell happened?

14:46.375 --> 14:50.667
Why didn't I see it coming?

14:50.709 --> 14:52.417
What am I missing?

15:02.959 --> 15:07.041
Kivas wishes you to wear

15:02.959 --> 15:07.041
this set of clothes

15:07.083 --> 15:09.542
and to sit

15:07.083 --> 15:09.542
in your chair.

15:09.583 --> 15:13.208
I have no reason to accede

15:09.583 --> 15:13.208
to Mr. Fajo's wishes.

15:13.250 --> 15:15.709
He will give

15:13.250 --> 15:15.709
you reasons

15:15.750 --> 15:17.959
if you force him to.

15:18.000 --> 15:22.125
Mr. Fajo is deluding himself if

15:18.000 --> 15:22.125
he believes he can keep me here.

15:22.166 --> 15:24.125
The<i> Enterprise</i> is certain

15:22.166 --> 15:24.125
to find me.

15:24.166 --> 15:26.000
They're not even

15:24.166 --> 15:26.000
looking for you.

15:26.041 --> 15:28.041
They think you're destroyed.

15:28.083 --> 15:30.083
Your shuttle blew up.

15:30.125 --> 15:32.250
A hytritium explosion.

15:32.291 --> 15:35.208
They will scan the debris and

15:32.291 --> 15:35.208
discover I was not aboard.

15:35.250 --> 15:37.208
They'll find exactly what they

15:35.250 --> 15:37.208
thought they'd find--

15:37.250 --> 15:39.792
traces of your

15:37.250 --> 15:39.792
component elements.

