15:39.834 --> 15:44.583
in just the right proportions.

15:46.834 --> 15:50.208
Clearly, Mr. Fajo

15:46.834 --> 15:50.208
has no moral difficulty

15:50.250 --> 15:51.542
with my imprisonment here.

15:51.583 --> 15:55.917
Mr. Fajo has

15:51.583 --> 15:55.917
no moral difficulties at all.

15:55.959 --> 15:58.709
Do you?

15:58.750 --> 16:01.041
Clever, android.

16:01.083 --> 16:04.166
Is it part of your program

16:01.083 --> 16:04.166
to seek out vulnerabilities

16:04.208 --> 16:05.417
in your enemies?

16:05.458 --> 16:08.542
Yes. Are you my enemy?

16:08.583 --> 16:12.083
I obey Fajo and so does everyone

16:08.583 --> 16:12.083
on this ship.

16:12.125 --> 16:13.458
Why?

16:13.500 --> 16:16.500
You are a curious thing,

16:13.500 --> 16:16.500
aren't you?

16:16.542 --> 16:18.917
Do you object to the question?

16:18.959 --> 16:22.625
Kivas finds ways to get

16:18.959 --> 16:22.625
what he wants from his people.

16:22.667 --> 16:26.333
His rewards for loyalty

16:22.667 --> 16:26.333
are lavish.

16:26.375 --> 16:33.208
His punishments for

16:26.375 --> 16:33.208
disloyalty are equally...

16:33.250 --> 16:35.208
lavish.

16:35.250 --> 16:37.542
You won't find anyone

16:37.583 --> 16:39.583
here on this ship

16:37.583 --> 16:39.583
to help you escape.

16:39.625 --> 16:42.000
Face it, android.

16:42.041 --> 16:44.041
He has you.

16:45.417 --> 16:48.083
It appears...

16:48.125 --> 16:50.333
he has us both.

16:59.208 --> 17:01.083
The reason

16:59.208 --> 17:01.083
I can't find anything

17:01.125 --> 17:03.166
is that there's

17:01.125 --> 17:03.166
nothing to find.

17:03.208 --> 17:05.166
I've run this analysis

17:03.208 --> 17:05.166
dozen's of times over,

17:05.208 --> 17:07.625
and there's just no indication

17:05.208 --> 17:07.625
of any malfunction.

17:07.667 --> 17:09.083
No explanation at all?

17:09.125 --> 17:11.959
Oh, yeah, there's one,

17:09.125 --> 17:11.959
but I don't believe it.

17:12.000 --> 17:14.041
Pilot error?

17:14.083 --> 17:16.542
I know it's hard to accept,

17:14.083 --> 17:16.542
but even the best...

17:16.583 --> 17:20.333
Captain, it's not only hard

17:16.583 --> 17:20.333
to accept with Data,

17:16.583 --> 17:20.333
it's impossible.

17:20.375 --> 17:23.834
I mean, I can't even begin

17:20.375 --> 17:23.834
to calculate the odds.

17:23.875 --> 17:25.250
It's...

17:25.291 --> 17:30.750
well, if Data were here,

17:25.291 --> 17:30.750
we could ask him.

17:31.917 --> 17:33.834
What are you suggesting,

17:31.917 --> 17:33.834
Lieutenant?

17:33.875 --> 17:35.583
I don't know, sir.

17:35.625 --> 17:39.583
It just doesn't

17:35.625 --> 17:39.583
make sense.

17:39.625 --> 17:41.959
And I like for things

17:39.625 --> 17:41.959
to make sense, that's all.

17:42.000 --> 17:44.875
Geordi, maybe if you got

17:42.000 --> 17:44.875
a little rest,

17:44.917 --> 17:46.917
and you came at this

17:44.917 --> 17:46.917
thing fresh.

17:46.959 --> 17:49.792
A little rest isn't going to

17:46.959 --> 17:49.792
change the computer analysis,

17:46.959 --> 17:49.792
Commander.

17:49.834 --> 17:52.834
I'm sure you have done

17:49.834 --> 17:52.834
a complete investigation,

17:52.875 --> 17:56.083
and if you wish to continue it,

17:52.875 --> 17:56.083
of course, you have my full

17:52.875 --> 17:56.083
support.

17:56.125 --> 18:00.125
But we shall be reaching

17:56.125 --> 18:00.125
the Beta Agni system shortly,

18:00.166 --> 18:03.375
and I expect you to be rested.

18:05.166 --> 18:08.417
I understand, sir.

18:08.458 --> 18:10.542
Dismissed.

18:12.583 --> 18:13.875
Geordi...

18:17.041 --> 18:21.333
I understand

18:17.041 --> 18:21.333
how much we want...

