29:26.125 --> 29:28.709
According to these figures,

29:26.125 --> 29:28.709
the 81 kilos

29:28.750 --> 29:31.458
of hytritium should be enough

29:28.750 --> 29:31.458
to neutralize the contamination.

29:31.500 --> 29:33.333
Now approaching target

29:31.500 --> 29:33.333
coordinates.

29:33.375 --> 29:34.709
Launch probe.

29:41.875 --> 29:43.917
Probe on target.

29:43.959 --> 29:46.542
Hytritium entering water table.

29:46.583 --> 29:51.166
Disbursement slightly

29:46.583 --> 29:51.166
faster than expected.

29:51.208 --> 29:54.917
Sir,

29:51.208 --> 29:54.917
something unusual.

29:54.959 --> 29:57.709
Specify.

29:57.750 --> 30:02.208
I'm getting concentrated

29:57.750 --> 30:02.208
tricyanate readings

30:02.250 --> 30:05.875
of 70 grams per cubic centimeter

30:02.250 --> 30:05.875
at the source coordinates--

30:05.917 --> 30:08.166
much higher than

30:05.917 --> 30:08.166
would normally occur.

30:08.208 --> 30:11.583
Computer, report on geological

30:08.208 --> 30:11.583
instability on Beta Agni Two.

30:11.625 --> 30:13.792
COMPUTER:

30:11.625 --> 30:13.792
No significant

30:11.625 --> 30:13.792
geological activity

30:13.834 --> 30:15.917
has been recorded

30:13.834 --> 30:15.917
on Beta Agni Two

30:15.959 --> 30:18.500
since the settlement of the

30:15.959 --> 30:18.500
Federation colony.

30:18.542 --> 30:22.291
Number One, perhaps you better

30:18.542 --> 30:22.291
take an away team down and have

30:18.542 --> 30:22.291
a closer look.

30:22.333 --> 30:23.625
Aye, sir.

30:23.667 --> 30:25.083
Dr. Crusher, join me

30:23.667 --> 30:25.083
in transporter room three.

30:25.125 --> 30:26.166
BEVERLY:

30:25.125 --> 30:26.166
On my way.

30:26.208 --> 30:27.709
Mr. Worf.

30:49.792 --> 30:56.208
I would very much like our

30:49.792 --> 30:56.208
relationship to...change.

30:56.250 --> 30:58.834
You may expect me to use every

30:56.250 --> 30:58.834
means at my disposal

30:58.875 --> 31:00.166
to resist your wishes.

31:02.000 --> 31:03.375
Why couldn't you just comply?

31:03.417 --> 31:06.166
Why do you have to argue

31:03.417 --> 31:06.166
all the time?

31:06.208 --> 31:08.709
Couldn't you just go sit

31:06.208 --> 31:08.709
on the chair?

31:10.792 --> 31:14.792
Come on, go sit on the chair.

31:14.834 --> 31:17.291
I do not intend to sit

31:14.834 --> 31:17.291
in the chair.

31:17.333 --> 31:19.417
You will.

31:19.458 --> 31:22.041
You may not believe it

31:19.458 --> 31:22.041
right now,

31:22.083 --> 31:24.667
but you will.

31:28.875 --> 31:29.875
Oh...

31:38.458 --> 31:41.709
Have you ever seen

31:38.458 --> 31:41.709
one of these, Data?

31:41.750 --> 31:43.375
It is a disrupter.

31:43.417 --> 31:48.208
Well...no, it's a prototype

31:43.417 --> 31:48.208
for a Varon-T disrupter.

31:48.250 --> 31:51.709
The Varon-T disrupter is banned

31:48.250 --> 31:51.709
in the Federation.

31:51.750 --> 31:54.667
Oh, yes, they only manufactured

31:51.750 --> 31:54.667
five of them. I own four.

31:54.709 --> 31:57.250
I sleep with one under my pillow

31:54.709 --> 31:57.250
at night, and I sleep very well

31:57.291 --> 31:58.959
knowing it's there, too.

31:59.000 --> 31:59.959
Do you know why?

32:00.000 --> 32:02.041
It is a most lethal weapon.

32:02.083 --> 32:05.792
It's not just lethal, it's...

32:05.834 --> 32:07.834
it's vicious.

32:07.875 --> 32:10.333
It tears a body apart,

32:07.875 --> 32:10.333
inside-out,

32:10.375 --> 32:13.542
and does it very slowly, too,

32:10.375 --> 32:13.542
by your phaser standards.

32:13.583 --> 32:20.375
It's a tortuous, very...

32:13.583 --> 32:20.375
very painful death.

32:20.417 --> 32:22.208
I've always wanted to try this.

32:22.250 --> 32:24.375
It is doubtful

32:22.250 --> 32:24.375
you will destroy me

32:24.417 --> 32:27.083
since you assign so much value

32:24.417 --> 32:27.083
to possessing me.

32:27.125 --> 32:29.667
That goes without saying.

32:33.083 --> 32:36.500
Please come in.

32:36.542 --> 32:41.166
Varria, how long have we

32:36.542 --> 32:41.166
been together, my dear?

32:41.208 --> 32:43.125
14 years.

32:43.166 --> 32:45.500
14 wonderful years

32:43.166 --> 32:45.500
they were, too.

32:45.542 --> 32:49.166
She was barely an adult

32:45.542 --> 32:49.166
when I found her.

32:49.208 --> 32:51.625
She was idealistic,

32:51.667 --> 32:53.959
naive and full of dreams

32:54.000 --> 32:56.750
and I made those dreams come

32:54.000 --> 32:56.750
true, too, didn't I?

32:56.792 --> 33:00.166
I'm going to miss you.

33:04.333 --> 33:06.166
DATA:

33:04.333 --> 33:06.166
Fajo.

33:27.041 --> 33:30.250
The contamination

33:27.041 --> 33:30.250
has been neutralized.

33:30.291 --> 33:31.250
The water is clean.

33:31.291 --> 33:33.041
WORF:

33:31.291 --> 33:33.041
Curious.

33:33.083 --> 33:36.083
The process of neutralization

33:33.083 --> 33:36.083
should have taken several hours.

33:36.125 --> 33:42.166
Naturally-occurring tricyanate

33:36.125 --> 33:42.166
does not respond this quickly.

33:42.208 --> 33:45.959
Are you saying

33:42.208 --> 33:45.959
it's not naturally occurring?

33:46.000 --> 33:48.417
There are no natural

33:46.000 --> 33:48.417
trace elements present

33:48.458 --> 33:50.000
in these tricyanate crystals.

33:50.041 --> 33:52.083
If it's artificial then we're

33:50.041 --> 33:52.083
talking about sabotage.

33:52.125 --> 33:54.083
BEVERLY:

33:52.125 --> 33:54.083
With tricyanate?

33:54.125 --> 33:55.709
That's hard to believe.

33:55.750 --> 33:59.083
It's slow to assimilate,

33:55.750 --> 33:59.083
difficult to replicate

33:59.125 --> 34:01.500
and hard to transport.

34:01.542 --> 34:05.125
There are a lot easier ways

34:01.542 --> 34:05.125
to poison a water supply.

34:05.166 --> 34:07.542
More effective ways, too.

34:07.583 --> 34:09.291
Can you think of any reason a

34:07.583 --> 34:09.291
saboteur

34:09.333 --> 34:10.750
would choose tricyanate?

34:10.792 --> 34:14.875
It might pass

34:10.792 --> 34:14.875
for a natural disaster.

34:14.917 --> 34:18.834
And since there's only one way

34:14.917 --> 34:18.834
to treat it, with hytritium,

34:18.875 --> 34:22.333
maybe somebody figured

34:18.875 --> 34:22.333
we couldn't locate it.

34:22.375 --> 34:23.792
It is hard to find.

34:23.834 --> 34:25.959
Then it really was

34:23.834 --> 34:25.959
lucky, wasn't it?

34:26.000 --> 34:28.333
That we were able to find

34:26.000 --> 34:28.333
hytritium when we did.

34:28.375 --> 34:31.500
And just enough hytritium

34:28.375 --> 34:31.500
for this crisis.

34:34.083 --> 34:37.542
Fajo was in the right place

34:34.083 --> 34:37.542
at the right time,

34:34.083 --> 34:37.542
just when we needed him most.

34:37.583 --> 34:40.583
Are you suggesting he created

34:37.583 --> 34:40.583
the problem just to solve it?

34:40.625 --> 34:41.750
Possibly.

34:41.792 --> 34:43.083
LA FORGE:

34:41.792 --> 34:43.083
What, to make a profit

34:43.125 --> 34:44.542
from his sale of hytritium?

34:44.583 --> 34:46.041
It doesn't add up.

34:46.083 --> 34:48.542
The cost of producing tricyanate

34:46.083 --> 34:48.542
is very expensive.

34:48.583 --> 34:50.667
He wouldn't make a profit on it.

34:50.709 --> 34:52.166
Quite the contrary.

34:52.208 --> 34:54.250
Then why would he do it?

34:54.291 --> 34:56.125
What did he want?

34:57.792 --> 35:01.333
Computer, biographical file

34:57.792 --> 35:01.333
on trader Kivas Fajo.

35:01.375 --> 35:03.125
COMPUTER:

35:01.375 --> 35:03.125
Accessing file.

35:03.166 --> 35:07.333
Kivas Fajo, a Zibalian trader

35:03.166 --> 35:07.333
of the Stacius trade guild

35:07.375 --> 35:09.083
educated on Iraatin Five.

35:09.125 --> 35:12.083
A noted collector

35:09.125 --> 35:12.083
of rare and valuable objects

35:12.125 --> 35:13.667
including the Rejac crystal,

35:13.709 --> 35:16.125
the<i> Starry Night</i> by Vincent

35:13.709 --> 35:16.125
Van Gogh,

35:16.166 --> 35:18.417
the Lawmin galactopedia,

35:18.458 --> 35:19.834
the Malia Manda tapestry...

35:19.875 --> 35:21.041
Computer, that is sufficient.

35:21.083 --> 35:23.417
A rare and valuable object.

35:23.458 --> 35:26.166
What if Data

35:23.458 --> 35:26.166
wasn't on that shuttle?

35:26.208 --> 35:27.500
Mr. Crusher.

35:27.542 --> 35:29.417
CRUSHER:

35:27.542 --> 35:29.417
Aye, sir.

35:29.458 --> 35:31.667
Set course for the site

35:29.458 --> 35:31.667
of the shuttlepod explosion.

35:29.458 --> 35:31.667
Warp eight.

35:31.709 --> 35:32.917
Aye, sir.

35:36.750 --> 35:40.125
The<i> Jovis</i> has a maximum speed

35:36.750 --> 35:40.125
of warp three.

35:40.166 --> 35:41.583
He's had 23 hours.

35:41.625 --> 35:45.583
So we can define a perimeter

35:41.625 --> 35:45.583
of .102 light-years

35:45.625 --> 35:46.917
as his possible distance

35:45.625 --> 35:46.917
distance.

35:46.959 --> 35:49.000
Fajo doesn't know that

35:46.959 --> 35:49.000
we're onto him.

35:49.041 --> 35:53.417
So he probably isn't taxing

35:49.041 --> 35:53.417
his engines top speed.

35:53.458 --> 35:55.542
He could have made it

35:53.458 --> 35:55.542
to the Nel Bato system

35:55.583 --> 35:57.917
or maybe even the Giles belt.

35:57.959 --> 35:59.750
He's a trader.

35:59.792 --> 36:02.208
He doesn't attract customers

35:59.792 --> 36:02.208
by being hard to find.

36:02.250 --> 36:04.917
We could put out a coded Level

36:02.250 --> 36:04.917
Two query to all Federation

36:02.250 --> 36:04.917
outposts

36:04.959 --> 36:06.375
within the perimeter.

36:06.417 --> 36:08.333
Make it so.

36:24.125 --> 36:29.417
If I help you escape,

36:24.125 --> 36:29.417
will you take me with you?

36:29.458 --> 36:30.959
He's sleeping.

36:31.000 --> 36:33.000
And there isn't

36:31.000 --> 36:33.000
much time.

36:33.041 --> 36:34.750
The consequences

36:33.041 --> 36:34.750
if we are caught...

36:34.792 --> 36:37.417
I know

36:34.792 --> 36:37.417
the consequences.

36:40.000 --> 36:42.333
14 years...

36:42.375 --> 36:44.959
you learn a few things.

36:46.959 --> 36:50.166
There's an escape pod

36:46.959 --> 36:50.166
in the aft cargo bay.

36:59.750 --> 37:04.333
Captain, affirmative response

36:59.750 --> 37:04.333
from station Lya-Four.

37:06.834 --> 37:09.834
Fajo spent more than

37:06.834 --> 37:09.834
half a day in orbit.

37:09.875 --> 37:12.291
Departed just over

37:09.875 --> 37:12.291
seven hours ago.

37:12.333 --> 37:14.250
Mr. Crusher, new coordinates.

37:14.291 --> 37:16.417
Lay in a course for Lya-Four.

37:16.458 --> 37:18.125
Course already

37:16.458 --> 37:18.125
laid in, sir.

37:22.250 --> 37:26.041
Perhaps I should attempt

37:22.250 --> 37:26.041
to communicate

37:22.250 --> 37:26.041
with the<i> Enterprise.</i>

37:26.083 --> 37:27.583
You can't.

37:27.625 --> 37:30.917
Fajo has communications access

37:27.625 --> 37:30.917
restricted to the bridge.

37:30.959 --> 37:34.625
Once we're out,

37:30.959 --> 37:34.625
the shuttle pod will emit

37:30.959 --> 37:34.625
an emergency beacon.

37:34.667 --> 37:36.875
We'll just have to hope

37:34.667 --> 37:36.875
somebody responds

37:36.917 --> 37:39.000
before Fajo is able

37:36.917 --> 37:39.000
to destroy us.

37:39.041 --> 37:41.166
I am trained

37:39.041 --> 37:41.166
in evasive maneuvers.

37:41.208 --> 37:43.667
We'll need a few.

37:43.709 --> 37:45.417
Let's get going.

37:46.959 --> 37:50.083
As soon as I start

37:46.959 --> 37:50.083
the escape sequence

37:50.125 --> 37:51.500
an alarm will sound.

37:51.542 --> 37:54.875
We won't have much time.

38:07.417 --> 38:11.208
(<i> alarm siren</i> )

38:21.625 --> 38:22.959
VARRIA:

38:21.625 --> 38:22.959
Oh, no!

39:37.458 --> 39:40.375
(<i> screaming</i> )

39:47.625 --> 39:50.041
It's your fault.

39:50.083 --> 39:52.667
You knew the price

39:50.083 --> 39:52.667
for disobedience.

39:52.709 --> 39:54.917
And so did she.

39:58.458 --> 40:01.917
Well, there's always

39:58.458 --> 40:01.917
another Varria.

40:19.375 --> 40:21.875
You won't hurt me.

40:21.917 --> 40:25.125
"Fundamental respect

40:21.917 --> 40:25.125
for all living beings."

40:25.166 --> 40:28.750
That's what you said.

40:28.792 --> 40:30.625
I'm a living being.

40:30.667 --> 40:33.083
Therefore, you can't harm me.

40:33.125 --> 40:36.625
You will surrender yourself

40:33.125 --> 40:36.625
to the authorities.

40:36.667 --> 40:39.792
Or what?

40:36.667 --> 40:39.792
You'll fire?

40:39.834 --> 40:42.583
Empty threat

40:39.834 --> 40:42.583
and we both know it.

40:42.625 --> 40:45.083
Why don't you

40:42.625 --> 40:45.083
accept your fate?

40:45.125 --> 40:46.959
You'll return

40:45.125 --> 40:46.959
to your chair

40:47.000 --> 40:48.709
and you will

40:47.000 --> 40:48.709
sit there.

40:48.750 --> 40:51.333
You will entertain me and you

40:48.750 --> 40:51.333
will entertain my guests.

40:51.375 --> 40:52.583
And if you don't,

40:52.625 --> 40:54.750
I'll simply kill

40:52.625 --> 40:54.750
someone else.

40:54.792 --> 40:57.166
Him, perhaps.

40:57.208 --> 40:59.458
Doesn't matter.

40:59.500 --> 41:01.000
Their blood will be

40:59.500 --> 41:01.000
on your hands, too,

41:01.041 --> 41:04.333
just like poor Varria's.

41:04.375 --> 41:07.500
Your only

41:04.375 --> 41:07.500
alternative, Data,

41:07.542 --> 41:10.041
is to fire.

41:10.083 --> 41:12.333
Murder me.

41:12.375 --> 41:13.667
That's all you have to do.

41:13.709 --> 41:17.250
Go ahead, fire.

41:17.291 --> 41:24.500
If only you could feel rage

41:17.291 --> 41:24.500
over Varria's death.

41:24.542 --> 41:28.542
If only you could feel

41:24.542 --> 41:28.542
a need for revenge,

41:28.583 --> 41:31.667
then maybe you could fire.

41:31.709 --> 41:35.041
But you're just an android.

41:35.083 --> 41:37.625
You can't feel

41:35.083 --> 41:37.625
anything, can you?

41:37.667 --> 41:41.959
It's just another interesting

41:37.667 --> 41:41.959
intellectual puzzle for you,

41:42.000 --> 41:46.625
another of life's curiosities.

41:46.667 --> 41:53.500
I cannot permit this

41:46.667 --> 41:53.500
to continue.

41:53.542 --> 41:56.750
Wait, your program

41:53.542 --> 41:56.750
won't allow you to fire.

41:56.792 --> 41:58.333
You can't fire.

41:58.375 --> 41:59.750
No.

42:05.125 --> 42:08.125
I'm reading a weapon

42:05.125 --> 42:08.125
in transit with commander Data.

42:08.166 --> 42:10.333
It seems to have

42:08.166 --> 42:10.333
discharged, sir.

42:10.375 --> 42:12.375
Discharged?

42:12.417 --> 42:14.333
I'm deactivating it.

42:23.917 --> 42:26.333
Welcome back, Mr. Data.

42:26.375 --> 42:28.041
Are you all right?

42:28.083 --> 42:29.500
Yes, Commander.

42:29.542 --> 42:33.041
Please arrange to have

42:29.542 --> 42:33.041
Kivas Fajo taken into custody

42:33.083 --> 42:36.709
on charges of murder,

42:33.083 --> 42:36.709
kidnapping, theft...

42:36.750 --> 42:39.166
The arrangements have

42:36.750 --> 42:39.166
already been made.

42:41.625 --> 42:45.417
A Varon-T disrupter.

42:45.458 --> 42:47.333
It belongs to Fajo.

42:47.375 --> 42:50.834
Mr. O'Brien says the weapon was

42:47.375 --> 42:50.834
in a state of discharge.

42:53.959 --> 42:57.959
Perhaps something occurred

42:53.959 --> 42:57.959
during transport, Commander.

43:17.542 --> 43:22.250
Oh, have you come

43:17.542 --> 43:22.250
to see me repent?

43:22.291 --> 43:25.375
Your final satisfaction?

43:25.417 --> 43:28.792
Want to see me

43:25.417 --> 43:28.792
beg for mercy?

43:28.834 --> 43:31.875
You're not going to get

43:28.834 --> 43:31.875
any of that from me.

43:31.917 --> 43:34.417
I expected nothing.

43:34.458 --> 43:39.125
Our roles are reversed.

43:39.166 --> 43:42.375
Aren't they, Data?

43:42.417 --> 43:43.458
You're the collector now.

43:43.500 --> 43:49.166
Me, I'm in a cage.

43:49.208 --> 43:50.750
So it seems.

43:50.792 --> 43:52.625
Don't count me out

43:50.792 --> 43:52.625
too quickly.

43:52.667 --> 43:53.875
I had you in my collection once.

43:53.917 --> 43:55.834
I can have you there again.

43:55.875 --> 43:58.125
Unlikely, sir.

43:59.959 --> 44:04.500
Your collection

43:59.959 --> 44:04.500
has been confiscated.

44:04.542 --> 44:06.083
All of your stolen possessions

44:06.125 --> 44:09.583
are being returned

44:06.125 --> 44:09.583
to their rightful owners.

44:09.625 --> 44:12.458
You have lost everything

44:09.625 --> 44:12.458
you value.

44:12.500 --> 44:15.166
That must give you

44:12.500 --> 44:15.166
great pleasure.

44:15.208 --> 44:20.667
No, sir, it does not.

44:20.709 --> 44:23.667
I do not feel pleasure.

44:23.709 --> 44:26.625
I am only an android.
